  "original_title": "\u0dbb\u0db1\u0dd2\u0dbd\u0dca \u0dc0\u0dd2\u0d9a\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0db8\u0dc3\u0dd2\u0d82\u0dc4:\u0dc0\u0dd0\u0da9\u0dd2 \u0da1\u0db1\u0dca\u0daf\u0dba\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca \u0d85\u0da7 \u0dc0\u0db1 \u0dc0\u0dd2\u0db0\u0dcf\u0dba\u0d9a \u0da2\u0db1\u0db4\u0dad\u0dd2 \u0dbd\u0dd9\u0dc3 \u0db4\u0dad\u0dca\u0dc0\u0dd9\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Ranil Wickramasinghe: Becomes the eighth Executive President with more votes",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Parliament General Secretary Dhammika Dasanayake said that Ranil Wickramasinghe was elected as the eighth Executive President by the majority of the members of the Parliament of Sri Lanka. The total number of votes he got is 134.",
        "Accordingly, today he won with a majority of 52 votes. Dallas lost 82 votes. Anura Kumara Dissanayake got 3 votes.",
        "Today (July 20) the voting began after the session of the Parliament started at 10 am, where the MKK MP cast their votes by calling out the name of each MP and the Speaker Mahinda Yapa Abeywardena was the first to vote, followed by the Prime Minister, Acting President Ranil. Wickramasinghe cast his vote.",
        "Samanpriya Herath and D. were two members of the Sri Lanka Podujana Peramuna who were very ill. Weerasinghe and elderly Dravida National Alliance leader R Sambandan were seen being taken to cast their votes with the help of parliamentary workers.",
        "Meanwhile, Selvaraja Kajendran and G. G. Ponnambalam abstained from casting his vote.",
        "During the counting of votes, four votes were declared invalid and the total number of valid votes declared today is 223."
      ],
